# Contributing to LoungeLex

Thank you for your interest in contributing to LoungeLex! We appreciate your help in making this bot better for everyone.

## How to Contribute

### Reporting Issues
- Before opening a new issue, please search the existing issues to avoid duplicates.
- Provide clear, detailed descriptions and steps to reproduce any bugs.

### Feature Requests
- Suggest new features by opening an issue with a clear explanation and potential use cases.
- Discuss with maintainers if you plan to work on a larger feature before submitting a pull request.

### Pull Requests
- Fork the repository and create your branch from `main`.
- Write clear, concise commit messages.
- Ensure your code follows the existing style and formatting.
- Test your changes thoroughly before submitting.
- Include relevant tests for new features or bug fixes.
- Open a pull request describing your changes in detail.

## Code Style
- Use modern JavaScript (ES6+) and follow the style used in the project.
- Keep functions small and focused.
- Write clear and meaningful comments where necessary.

## License
By contributing, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under the [MIT License](LICENSE).

---

Thank you for helping improve LoungeLex!
